Rio’s Diamond Output at Zimbabwean Mine Rises 83%, Mail Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-10-23T10:06:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/rio-s-diamond-output-at-zimbabwean-mine-rises-83-mail-reports.html
Diamond production at  Rio Tinto
Plc (RIO) ’s Murowa mine in  Zimbabwe  rose 83 percent from a year
earlier in the nine months to Sept. 30, reaching 254,000 carats,
the state-controlled  Sunday Mail  said, citing a company report.  The mine dug 93,000 carats in the third quarter, 10 percent
less than in the previous three-month period, the Harare-based
newspaper said on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 